891
01:01:14,564 --> 01:01:16,031
Good night.

892
01:01:21,036 --> 01:01:22,037
Oh, good night, kid.

893
01:01:56,071 --> 01:01:58,073
Court seems real nice.

894
01:01:59,574 --> 01:02:01,326
He kiss you yet?

895
01:02:01,361 --> 01:02:03,078
All the time.

896
01:02:04,579 --> 01:02:07,582
Is he a good kisser?

897
01:02:07,617 --> 01:02:09,084
He's all right.

898
01:02:25,100 --> 01:02:26,101
Shit.

899
01:02:39,114 --> 01:02:40,115
Hey.

900
01:02:45,620 --> 01:02:48,623
I was just going
down to the pond.

901
01:02:50,792 --> 01:02:52,092
You want to go?

902
01:02:52,127 --> 01:02:53,628
I've got work
up to my eyeballs

903
01:02:53,663 --> 01:02:55,130
and no end in sight.

904
01:02:55,296 --> 01:02:57,132
There's nobody
to tell me how to do it.

905
01:02:57,167 --> 01:02:58,633
It all depends on me.

906
01:02:59,134 --> 01:03:01,386
I can't play
whenever you want to.

907
01:03:01,421 --> 01:03:03,638
You don't have
to sound so hateful.

908
01:03:03,673 --> 01:03:04,639
I don't have time!

909
01:03:05,140 --> 01:03:06,641
Sorry I took your time.

910
01:03:07,142 --> 01:03:08,643
Maybe if you were
a little bit older,

911
01:03:08,678 --> 01:03:10,110
you'd understand.

912
01:03:10,145 --> 01:03:12,647
If I were older,
I could do everything,

913
01:03:12,682 --> 01:03:14,482
couldn't I, Court?

914
01:03:16,484 --> 01:03:18,653
I love you, Court.

915
01:03:18,987 --> 01:03:19,619
Don't.

916
01:03:19,654 --> 01:03:21,121
Don't love me now

917
01:03:21,156 --> 01:03:23,658
when things
are so mixed up.

918
01:03:23,693 --> 01:03:25,125
I've got more

919
01:03:25,160 --> 01:03:27,879
than I can say grace
over right now.

920
01:03:48,183 --> 01:03:49,482
You look real nice.

921
01:03:49,517 --> 01:03:52,687
I think I'll go out
for a little while.

922
01:03:52,722 --> 01:03:55,690
You going over
to the Trants' again?

923
01:03:55,725 --> 01:03:56,691
I might.

924
01:03:57,192 --> 01:03:59,694
I saw Maureen
at the hospital today.

925
01:04:00,195 --> 01:04:02,697
That girl
sure is turning out.

926
01:04:03,198 --> 01:04:04,199
You see Matt,

927
01:04:04,699 --> 01:04:06,701
you tell him
to holler at me

928
01:04:06,736 --> 01:04:07,702
if he needs anything.

929
01:04:08,203 --> 01:04:08,703
Yes, ma'am.

930
01:04:09,204 --> 01:04:10,288
Ok, guys, let's go!

931
01:04:10,705 --> 01:04:11,706
Get out. Come on.

932
01:04:12,207 --> 01:04:14,209
I'll see
you later, ok?

933
01:04:28,223 --> 01:04:30,225
My, my, my.

934
01:04:33,228 --> 01:04:34,194
Night-night.

935
01:04:34,229 --> 01:04:37,232
Ok, we're going
to go night-night.

936
01:04:37,267 --> 01:04:39,234
Oh, there we go.

937
01:04:39,734 --> 01:04:41,736
There we go.

938
01:04:43,238 --> 01:04:44,739
Here's your doll.

939
01:05:04,759 --> 01:05:05,760
Court.

940
01:05:08,263 --> 01:05:09,514
Hello.

941
01:05:09,549 --> 01:05:10,765
Hi.

942
01:05:12,767 --> 01:05:14,269
Dani is
at the hospital

943
01:05:14,769 --> 01:05:18,773
if you want to run on down
and visit with her.

944
01:05:19,274 --> 01:05:20,775
I don't think so.

945
01:05:23,778 --> 01:05:26,781
It, uh, sure was
a nice day.

946
01:05:26,816 --> 01:05:28,748
Yeah.

947
01:05:28,783 --> 01:05:30,785
Looks like
it's going to be

948
01:05:30,820 --> 01:05:32,252
a nice night, too.

949
01:05:32,287 --> 01:05:34,289
Looks like.
Yeah, looks like.

950
01:05:36,791 --> 01:05:40,295
I'll sure be glad when
I can leave this place

951
01:05:40,330 --> 01:05:42,064
and take you with me.

952
01:05:42,099 --> 01:05:43,763
Why don't you go home

953
01:05:43,798 --> 01:05:46,300
and get some sleep
for a change?

954
01:05:46,335 --> 01:05:48,803
I'll see you
in the morning.

955
01:05:53,808 --> 01:05:55,810
Call me
if anything happens.

956
01:05:55,845 --> 01:05:56,828
Yes, sir.

957
01:05:56,863 --> 01:05:57,812
I will.

958
01:06:15,330 --> 01:06:16,831
Thanks.

959
01:06:18,833 --> 01:06:20,835
So, do you like Elvis?

960
01:06:20,870 --> 01:06:21,801
Sure.

961
01:06:21,836 --> 01:06:23,303
Who doesn't?

962
01:06:23,338 --> 01:06:25,805
Dani absolutely
adores him.

963
01:06:25,840 --> 01:06:28,843
Well, she did
until you came along.

964
01:06:28,878 --> 01:06:29,809
You...

965
01:06:29,844 --> 01:06:31,846
pretty well shot Elvis
out of the saddle.

966
01:06:37,352 --> 01:06:38,818
I can't believe

967
01:06:38,853 --> 01:06:40,855
my little sister
is grown-up enough

968
01:06:40,890 --> 01:06:42,357
to have a boyfriend.

969
01:06:42,857 --> 01:06:45,860
It's not quite
exactly like that.

970
01:06:45,895 --> 01:06:46,826
I mean...

971
01:06:46,861 --> 01:06:49,864
it's more like
we're sort of buddies.

972
01:06:49,899 --> 01:06:52,867
Just...
real close buddies.

973
01:06:53,868 --> 01:06:56,120
Does Dani know that?

974
01:06:56,155 --> 01:06:58,373
I tried to tell her.

975
01:07:00,375 --> 01:07:02,377
You like her a lot?

976
01:07:02,412 --> 01:07:04,379
Of course I like her.

977
01:07:04,879 --> 01:07:06,381
I mean, she's...

978
01:07:07,382 --> 01:07:08,883
special.

979
01:07:09,050 --> 01:07:09,884
Oh.

980
01:07:10,885 --> 01:07:12,887
Yeah, she, um...

981
01:07:13,888 --> 01:07:15,390
she is that.

982
01:07:23,563 --> 01:07:26,566
But what if
I met someone else...

983
01:07:26,733 --> 01:07:29,569
someone special
in a different sort of way?

984
01:07:30,570 --> 01:07:32,537
Someone...

985
01:07:32,572 --> 01:07:34,574
she's my sister.

986
01:07:46,586 --> 01:07:50,089
If you...
need a friend,

987
01:07:50,124 --> 01:07:53,593
I make
a pretty good one.

988
01:07:55,095 --> 01:07:58,098
A friend's not what
I need right now.

989
01:08:16,116 --> 01:08:18,118
You better go.

990
01:09:11,171 --> 01:09:12,672
Daddy!
The hospital called.

991
01:09:12,707 --> 01:09:14,924
Mama's having the baby.

992
01:09:16,676 --> 01:09:19,679
All right.
I'm on my way.

993
01:09:19,714 --> 01:09:20,680
Ok.

994
01:09:29,689 --> 01:09:32,192
I'm glad you're the one
here with me.

995
01:09:32,692 --> 01:09:33,693
Me, too, mama.

996
01:09:34,194 --> 01:09:35,662
You're not frightened?

997
01:09:35,697 --> 01:09:36,947
No, mama.

998
01:09:36,982 --> 01:09:38,163
Good.

999
01:09:38,198 --> 01:09:39,664
Are you scared?

1000
01:09:39,699 --> 01:09:42,702
Not a bit.
I've done this before,

1001
01:09:43,036 --> 01:09:44,704
remember?

1002
01:09:44,739 --> 01:09:46,706
Aah.

1003
01:10:45,765 --> 01:10:47,267
Lord, Court.

1004
01:10:55,858 --> 01:10:58,243
Hope you ordered
a girl, Abigail.

1005
01:10:58,278 --> 01:11:01,781
I know someone who's going
to be mighty disappointed.

1006
01:11:01,816 --> 01:11:04,784
Matt had his heart
set on a boy.

1007
01:11:04,819 --> 01:11:07,287
Want me
to put it back?

1008
01:11:07,322 --> 01:11:08,288
God, no.

1009
01:11:11,291 --> 01:11:12,292
Court!

1010
01:11:13,793 --> 01:11:15,795
Hey, Court!
Where are you?

1011
01:11:18,798 --> 01:11:20,265
Court!

1012
01:11:20,300 --> 01:11:21,766
We've got a girl!

1013
01:11:21,801 --> 01:11:23,803
She's just
the tiniest thing

1014
01:11:23,838 --> 01:11:25,322
and perfect all over,

1015
01:11:25,357 --> 01:11:26,771
